  "notes": "Fletching requires a knife for cutting logs into bows and arrow shafts. Arrow shafts can be made from logs - higher tier logs produce more shafts per log (15 for normal, 30 for oak, 45 for willow, 60 for maple, 75 for yew, 90 for magic). Feathers are attached to shafts to make headless arrows, then arrowheads are added to create complete arrows. Bows must be strung with bow strings after being cut. Crossbows require stocks (fletched from logs), limbs (smithed from metal bars), and crossbow strings. Darts, javelins, and bolts are members-only. Some items require quest completion (bronze darts require The Tourist Trap)."
}
